  "local_port": 46738,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I downgrade Youtube on my Android Phone?",
  "response": "Downgrading the YouTube app on your Android device involves uninstalling updates to revert to the factory version that came with your phone. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### For Android 10 and Below:\n1. **Go to Settings:**\n   - Open the **Settings** app on your Android device.\n\n2. **Navigate to Apps or Application Manager:**\n   - Depending on your device, look for **Apps**, **Applications**, or **Application Manager** in the Settings menu.\n\n3. **Find YouTube:**\n   - Scroll through the list of installed apps and find **YouTube**.\n\n4. **Uninstall Updates:**\n   - Tap on **YouTube** to open its settings.\n   - Look for the **More Options** (three vertical dots) in the YouTube app info and tap **Uninstall Updates**.\n   - A confirmation prompt will appear; confirm by tapping **OK**.\n\n### For Android 11 and Above:\nIf you don\u2019t see the **Uninstall Updates** option (common in newer Android versions), follow these steps:\n1. **Open Google Play Store:**\n   - Launch the **Google Play Store** app on your device.\n\n2. **Search for YouTube:**\n   - Search for the **YouTube** app in the Play Store.\n\n3. **Uninstall Updates via Play Store:**\n   - If the app is already installed, you\u2019ll see an **Uninstall** button. Tap it to uninstall updates and revert to the factory version.\n\n### Alternative Method (Using ADB):\nIf the above methods don\u2019t work, you can use **ADB** (Android Debug Bridge) to uninstall updates:\n1. **Enable Developer Options:**\n   - Go to **Settings > About Phone** and tap **Build Number** seven times to enable Developer Options.\n\n2. **Enable USB Debugging:**\n   - Go to **Settings > System > Developer Options** and enable **USB Debugging**.\n\n3. **Connect Your Phone to a Computer:**\n   - Use a USB cable to connect your phone to a computer with ADB installed.\n\n4. **Run Command:**\n   - Open a Command Prompt or Terminal on your computer and run:\n     ```\n     adb shell pm uninstall -k --user 0 com.google.android.youtube\n     ```\n   - This will remove the updated version of the app and revert it to the factory version.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Factory Version Limitations:** The factory version of YouTube may lack newer features and could be outdated.\n- **Automatic Updates:** Disable automatic updates in the Play Store to prevent the app from updating again:\n  - Go to **Google Play Store > Profile > Settings > Network Preferences > Auto-update Apps** and select **Don't auto-update apps**.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
